com.avaje.ebean.annotation

Annotation Type Index


  • @Target(value={TYPE,FIELD})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Index
    An annotation for declaring an index on a single column.
    Author:
    rvbiljouw

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String[] columnNames
      When placed on the class (rather than field) you can specify the columns to include in the index in order.
      String name
      Name of the index.
      boolean unique
      If set true indicates this is a unique index.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract String name
        Name of the index. If left blank a name is derived using the built in naming convention.
        Default:
        ""

      • unique

        public abstract boolean unique
        If set true indicates this is a unique index.
        Default:
        false

      • columnNames

        public abstract String[] columnNames
        When placed on the class (rather than field) you can specify the columns to include in the index in order.
        Default:
        {}
